==English==

===Etymology===
{{AS.}} ''[[westweard]]''.  See [[west]], and [[-ward]].

===Adjective===
'''westward'''
# Lying toward the west.
#:''Yond same star that's '''westward''' from the pole.''  -[[Shak]].

[[category:English adjectives]]

===Adverb===
'''westward'''
# Toward the west; as, to ride or sail westward.
#:'''''Westward''' the course of empire takes its way.''  -Berkeley.

[[Category: English adverbs]]

===Noun===
'''westward'''
# The western region or countries; the west. 

[[category:English nouns]]